{
  "stem": "10572.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they knew that we were Jewish and they were somehow giving this award in spite of that tendency that existed that time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it gave us-- it gave us fuel for the things-- for the kind of engine we wanted to run.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We wanted to believe that this was not going to last, and we were encouraged by this, by many of our Christian friends who would come to us and say, don't give in.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This cannot last, until it was too late.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, yes, yes, indeed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You couldn't have helped it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, we-- we lived in this town, in this small town, relatively small town, even though, you know, the town of 75,000 in those days, we had our own theater.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had our own opera.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was not like a small town in America.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had gone to-- as I mentioned before, I had gone to this gymnasium was a Catholic school was under the sponsorship of the bishop of Hildesheim.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we would get encouragement from our teachers who were priests, who-- and by the very fact that they were priests were basically anti-Nazis.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we would be talked to, and-- and-- and I was once called in by a man who lived near the cathedral.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Our school was an adjunct to the cathedral, and this man was professor Konrad Agermussen, who had written a book, It was a book fighting the myth of the 20th century, which was the Nazi Bible.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it took an unbelievable amount of courage for him to do this, risking his future, his physical future.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one day, one of our workers was his cousin, Franz Kemner.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Franz Kemner asked me one day that Dr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Agermussen had asked him, would I come to see him?",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
